simple_means.memory_skill: chor 歌，舞 + us 表名词，用于科学术语 → 合唱（队）

tr: the part of a song where a soloist is joined by a group of singers
any utterance produced simultaneously by a group
a group of people assembled to sing together
a company of actors who comment (by speaking or singing in unison) on the action in a classical Greek play
a body of dancers or singers who perform together

value.def: A chorus is a part of a song which is repeated after each verse.

example.ex: Caroline sang two verses and the chorus of her song...
example.tran: 卡罗琳唱了她歌曲中的两段和副歌部分。
唱到副歌时，大家都跟着一起唱起来。

value.def: A chorus is a large group of people who sing together.

example.ex: The chorus was singing 'The Ode to Joy'.

value.def: A chorus is a piece of music written to be sung by a large group of people.
A chorus is a group of singers or dancers who perform together in a show, in contrast to the soloists.

example.ex: Students played the lesser parts and sang in the chorus.
example.tran: 学生扮演一些次要角色，并且参与合唱。

value.def: When there is a chorus of criticism, disapproval, or praise, that attitude is expressed by a lot of people at the same time.

example.ex: The government is defending its economic policies against a growing chorus of criticism.
example.tran: 面对日渐高涨的齐声指责，政府不断为其经济政策辩护。

value.tran: 齐声，异口同声(表示批评、反对或赞扬)

value.def: When people chorus something, they say it or sing it together.

example.ex: He was greeted with a rousing chorus of Happy Birthday...
example.tran: 迎接他的是大家齐唱《祝你生日快乐》，令他非常感动。

example.ex: 'All the best,' called the other typists in chorus.
example.tran: “祝万事如意，”其他打字员齐声喊道。
